.TH "ipr_slave_alloc" 9 "ipr_slave_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_slave_alloc \- Prepare for commands to a device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ipr_slave_alloc
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
scsi device struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function saves a pointer to the resource entry
in the scsi device struct if the device exists. We
can then use this pointer in ipr_queuecommand when
handling new commands.

Return value:
0 on success / -ENXIO if device does not exist
